The film featured Ashley Judd as Norma Jean Dougherty and Mira Sorvino as Marilyn Monroe.
It was partially-based on "Norma Jean: My Secret Life With Marilyn Monroe" by actor Ted Jordan (played by Josh Charles), who claimed to have had a years-long relationship with Monroe.
